            <title>[LUCENE-1280] NPE in PhraseQuery.toString(String f)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1280</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the section&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public String toString(String f) {&lt;br/&gt;
    StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer();&lt;br/&gt;
    if (!field.equals(f)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
      buffer.append(field);
      buffer.append(&quot;:&quot;);
    }
&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;snip&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;should be&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public String toString(String f) {&lt;br/&gt;
    StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer();&lt;br/&gt;
    if (field != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !field.equals(f)) &lt;/p&gt;
{
      buffer.append(field);
      buffer.append(&quot;:&quot;);
    }
&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;snip&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The issue arises if a phrase query is created, no terms are added, then the phrase query is added to a boolean query. Calling toString on the boolean query will result in a NPE insdie of the PhraseQuery.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
